A flat focusing POPA. (a) Diagrammatic sketch showing the working mechanisms and the position of the focal spot. Two nanostrips are working together to harness those nanopatches. (b) E-field intensity distribution on the xoz plane with respect to which the array is symmetric. In this design, Hp = 100, Tp = 50, Rp = 140, Hs = 600, Ts = 100, Ws = 200 and h = 700, all in nm. (c) E-field intensity distribution on a cut-plane 3.6 μm above the polymer film, showing a diffraction-limited focal spot. The FWHM of the focal spot is 1.25 μm (wavelength:1550 nm).
